Russian Equity Movers: M.Video, Norilsk Nickel, Lukoil

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-09-06T15:11:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-06/russian-equity-movers-m-video-norilsk-nickel-lukoil.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  advanced
0.5 percent to 1,499.70 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow. The
dollar-denominated RTS Index added 0.1 percent to 1,618.63.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  M.Video (MVID RX), a Russian electronics retailer, climbed
for a third day after Vedomosti reported Czech private equity
firm PPF Group NV may acquire a controlling stake in the
company. The shares increased as much as 4 percent and closed up
0.9 percent at 223.96 rubles.  OAO GMK Norilsk Nickel (GMKN RX) advanced for a second day
after United Co. Rusal yesterday rejected Norilsk’s $8.75
billion offer for the 15 percent stake Rusal owns in Russia’s
largest miner. Norilsk may make the same buyback offer to all
shareholders in one to two weeks, UralSib Financial Corp.
analyst Dmitry Smolin said. The shares gained as much as 2.2
percent and closed 1.2 percent higher at 7,167 rubles.  OAO Lukoil (LKOH RX), Russia’s second-largest oil producer,
rallied for the first day in four, adding 1.2 percent to
1,720.70 rubles. Brent futures snapped a three-day losing streak
as the dollar plunged after the Swiss central bank said it’s
imposing a ceiling on the franc’s exchange rate with the euro.  To contact the reporter on this story:
